A Judiciary executive officer was charged on Friday with demanding a Sh2,000 bribe to set a hearing date for a woman's case.Michael Odoyo, of the Milimani family division, allegedly committed the crime on December 14, 2014 at Milimani law courts in Nairobi.Odoyo is said to have demanded the amount from a woman named Lilian Chilande to retrieve her succession court file and fix the date.The court heard that the officer said he would also assist Chilande in obtaining letters of administration.Odoyo has been admitted at Kenyatta National Hospital since January last year.He denied three counts of corruption in the case heard by Milimani Anti-Corruption Court principal magistrate Felix Kombo.Kombo granted him a personal bond of Sh100,000 pending the hearing on March 2, 2017.